# backup-util

Manage backups easily, including automatic detection of system config
files customised by the user.

## Pre-use

Depends: rsnapshot (>= 1.3.1), debsums, dlocate

You may also need to patch rsnapshot:
- if using upstream 1.3.1, you need to apply [1], [2]
- if using debian 1.3.1-1, you need to apply [1], [2]
- if using debian 1.3.1-2 or -3, you need to apply [2]

[1] http://rsnapshot.cvs.sourceforge.net/viewvc/rsnapshot/rsnapshot/rsnapshot-program.pl?r1=1.400&r2=1.401&view=patch
[2] http://rsnapshot.cvs.sourceforge.net/viewvc/rsnapshot/rsnapshot/rsnapshot-program.pl?r1=1.405&r2=1.406&view=patch

## Use

See `./backup-util` for instructions on use.

# apt-pkg

Keeps track of the "important" parts of aptitude package state.

## Pre-use

$ git init pkg-backup && cd pkg-backup
$ touch packages.txt && git add packages.txt
$ git commit -m "touch package state"

## Use

$ /path/to/apk-pkg c
